Yes. I believe that focusing on the President's awareness of his own anomalous provenance has a great deal of potential in terms of narrative and character development. Given that this is already a dialogue-heavy article, I could see this effectively explore themes such as self-doubt, legitimacy, and national sovereignty in the context of the colonial heritage of the nations of the Caribbean/Americas. Of course, this is speaking in broad terms; how this may look like in terms of the specific progression of the story is up to you, but I feel like the pieces are here.







